  "texts": [
    "Consequently, a large-scale 3D-PCPR method named MinkLoc3D was introduced by Komorowski (2021).",
    "MinkLoc3D leverages a sparse voxelized point cloud representation and sparse 3D convolutions to compute a discriminative 3D point cloud descriptor, as depicted in Fig. 5.",
    "The efficacy of this method can be attributed to two key factors.",
    "Firstly, the sparse convolutional architecture effectively generates informative local features.",
    "Secondly, enhancements in the training process facilitate efficient and effective training by accommodating larger batch sizes."
  ],
